Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 25 December 2025
Last Updated: 25 December 2025

This Privacy Policy explains how Medication Reminder (“we”, “our”, “the App”) collects, uses, stores, and protects your information when you use our iOS application.

We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your data transparently and securely.

1. Information We Collect

We collect only the information necessary to provide medication reminder and adherence features.

1.1 Personal Information

Email address (used for login, account identification, and recovery)

User ID (generated by Firebase Authentication)

1.2 Medication & Health-Related Data

Medication names (e.g., Paracetamol, Dolo)

Dosage information (e.g., 650mg)

Medication schedules (time, frequency, course duration)

Medication intake status (taken, snoozed, skipped)

Streak and adherence analytics

Optional medication photos (pill image, strip/sheet image)

⚠️ We do not provide medical advice. All data is user-entered and used only for reminders and tracking.

1.3 Caretaker Information (Optional)

Caretaker name

Relationship (e.g., family, guardian)

Notification preferences

Push notification tokens (FCM), if enabled

1.4 Device & App Data

App usage events (for analytics and debugging)

Push notification tokens

App version and OS version (for stability and support)

2. How We Use Your Data

We use your data only to operate and improve the app.

Specifically, we use data to:

Schedule medication reminders and notifications

Display medication details and images

Provide voice reminders and call-style alerts

Track medication adherence and streaks

Notify caretakers when a dose is taken, missed, or skipped

Securely sync your data across devices

Improve app reliability, performance, and user experience

We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal or health-related data.

3. Data Storage & Security
3.1 Firebase Security

We use Google Firebase to store and protect your data:

Firebase Authentication for secure user login

Cloud Firestore for encrypted data storage

Firebase Storage for medication images

Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) for notifications

3.2 Protection Measures

All data is transmitted using HTTPS/TLS encryption

Firestore security rules restrict access to only your account

Each user can access only their own medication data

Access tokens and credentials are managed securely by Firebase

Despite strong security measures, no system is 100% secure. We continuously monitor and improve our security practices.

4. Third-Party Services

We rely on the following trusted third-party services:

Google Firebase (by Google LLC)

Authentication

Cloud Firestore

Cloud Storage

Cloud Messaging

Crash and performance monitoring (optional)

Firebase Privacy Policy:
https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy

We do not share your data with advertisers or data brokers.

5. User Rights & Controls

You have full control over your data.

You have the right to:

Access your personal and medication data

Edit or update your medication information

Delete medications, photos, and schedules

Export your data (upon request)

Delete your account, which permanently removes your data

Account Deletion

When you delete your account:

All personal data

Medication records

Photos

Analytics and streak data
are permanently deleted from our systems.

6. Data Retention

We retain your data only as long as your account is active.

Inactive accounts retain data until deletion

Deleted accounts trigger permanent data removal

Backup retention follows Firebase’s standard secure policies

7. Children’s Privacy

Medication Reminder may be used for children under adult supervision.

We do not knowingly collect data from children without guardian involvement

Caretaker features are designed to support guardians and parents

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.

Changes will be reflected with a new “Last Updated” date

Significant changes will be communicated within the app

9. Contact Information

If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding your privacy or data:

Email: support@medicationreminder.app

Developer: Pavan Kumar
App Name: Medication Reminder
